85_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-286_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-288_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-289_ pf-text-1">According to the Health Foundation, implementing person-centred care could lead to significant cost savings, with potential savings of £1.4 billion per year in the UK.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-291_ pf-text-1">Research published in the British Journal of General Practice suggests that person-centred care can improve patient satisfaction, treatment adherence, and health outcomes.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-293_ pf-text-1">A survey by the Care Quality Commission found that 84% of people receiving care at home reported that staff treated them with dignity and respect.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-295_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710431109" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710431109 1536w" width="1612" height="1228" alt="Mastering Person-Centred Care: A Guide to Social Care Excellence - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mastering Person-Centred Care: A Guide to Social Care Excellence - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-296_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-297_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-299_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-300_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_the_Person-Centred_Approach_Transforming_Social_Care_Practices_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267628" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_the_Person-Centred_Approach_Transforming_Social_Care_Practices_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267628 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Navigating the Person-Centred Approach: Transforming Social Care Practices - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Navigating the Person-Centred Approach: Transforming Social Care Practices - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-301_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-302_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by astakhovyaroslav via Envato Elements</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-304_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-305_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-307_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Person-centred care in social care involves tailoring support and services to meet the individual needs, preferences, and goals of each person receiving care, promoting autonomy, dignity, and respect. It's about seeing the person beyond their condition or circumstances and ensuring their voice is heard in every aspect of their care journey.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-309_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-310_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-311_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practices</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-313_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-314_ pf-text-1">The Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations set out the standards providers must meet to ensure the safety and well-being of individuals receiving care.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-316_ pf-text-1">The Care Quality Commission (CQC) Fundamental Standards emphasise the importance of dignity, respect, and individualised support in care provision.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-318_ pf-text-1">Best practice guidance from organisations like Skills for Care provides frameworks and resources for implementing effective person-centred care practices.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-320_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Individualised_Care_Elevating_Dignity_and_Respect_in_Social_Care_Settings_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267738" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Individualised_Care_Elevating_Dignity_and_Respect_in_Social_Care_Settings_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267738 1536w" width="1000" height="635" alt="Individualised Care: Elevating Dignity and Respect in Social Care Settings - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Individualised Care: Elevating Dignity and Respect in Social Care Settings - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-321_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-322_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by dvatri&nbsp;via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-324_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-325_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_Autonomy_in_Care_Key_Principles_and_Practices_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267841" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Empowering_Autonomy_in_Care_Key_Principles_and_Practices_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267841 1536w" width="1000" height="1499" alt="Empowering Autonomy in Care: Key Principles and Practices - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empowering Autonomy in Care: Key Principles and Practices - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-326_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-327_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  Wavebreakmedia

 via Envato Elements</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-329_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-330_ pf-heading-1-h3">Empowering person-centred care - Transforming social care practices</h3><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-332_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Understanding the essence of person-centred care</strong></p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-334_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Person-centred care is not just a set of procedures; it's a philosophy that shapes every interaction and decision within social care settings. It acknowledges that each individual has unique preferences, beliefs, and aspirations. By embracing PCC, caregivers shift their focus from tasks to relationships, from compliance to compassion.</p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-336_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>The impact of person-centred care</strong></p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-338_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Effective person-centred care has a ripple effect that extends far beyond the individual receiving care. It fosters a culture of respect and empowerment within organisations, leading to higher staff morale, improved job satisfaction, and improved outcomes for service users. Research has shown that individuals who receive person-centred care are more likely to report feeling valued, respected, and involved in decisions about their care.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-340_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-341_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-342_ pf-heading-1-h3">Implementing person-centred care - Best practices</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-344_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-345_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and education</strong> - Investing in staff training is critical to embedding person-centred care practices within organisations. The Mandatory Training Group offers accredited courses that equip caregivers with the skills and knowledge to deliver effective PCC.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-347_ pf-text-1"><strong>Leadership and culture</strong> - Leaders play a crucial role in setting the tone for person-centred care. They foster an environment where PCC thrives by setting an example of openness, collaboration, and continuous improvement.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-349_ pf-text-1"><strong>Communication and engagement</strong> - Effective communication lies at the heart of person-centred care. Encouraging open dialogue, actively listening to service users, and involving them in care decisions are essential components of PCC.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-351_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Care_Planning_Essentials_Enhancing_Communication_and_Collaboration_in_Social_Care_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267998" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Care_Planning_Essentials_Enhancing_Communication_and_Collaboration_in_Social_Care_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1713267998 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Care Planning Essentials: Enhancing Communication and Collaboration in Social Care - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Care Planning Essentials: Enhancing Communication and Collaboration in Social Care - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Train